
<p>lite2do 1.1.1 has been released! This release introduces improved
<code>help</code> and <code>list</code> commands as well as the addition of
<code>groups</code> command to display groups in the task list. See the
complete list of changes below.</p>

<!-- break -->

<h3>Features</h3>

<ul>
  <li>Heavily improved behaviour of <code>help</code> command. When the
    command name is supplied (e.g. <code>lite2do help list</code>),
    further information on its usage are displayed.</li>
  <li>Extended capabilities of <code>list</code>, making it possible to
    display the task with selected ID only.</li>
  <li>Added <code>groups</code> (or <code>gr</code> for short) command to
    display list of groups in the task list along with number of tasks that
    belong to each of them.</li>
  <li>Added <code>ud</code> as a short variant of <code>undo</code>
    command.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Bug Fixes</h3>

<ul>
  <li>It is no longer possible to successfully save an invalid group name,
    which usually resulted in corrupted save file and even unexpected
    crashes.</li>
  <li>Invalid colour is no longer accepted blindly and proper error message
    is displayed.</li>
</ul>
